com.camerontec.util.datamodel

Interface Field

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Encodable, FieldValue, IntKeyed, Nullable, OrderedCollection<FieldGroup>, OrderedCollectionOfFieldGroups, Recyclable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    NullField

    public interface Field
extends IntKeyed, OrderedCollectionOfFieldGroups, FieldValue
    Interface specifying the capabilities of a data field.

    Fields have the following characteristics:

    • A single integer key (at any particular time) in the range specified by [IntKeyed.MIN_KEY, IntKeyed.MAX_KEY]
    • A single value (at any particular point in time)
    • A managed lifecycle which is attached to the scope of its owning Message
    • An, optional, collection of nested field groups.

    A special property of this interface and its implementation is that any method which returns an object return value must guarantee never to return null.

    In terms of lifecycle management, clients must not assume it is safe to store a reference to a Field (or FieldGroup) unless it can be guaranteed that the original owning Message will not be recycled for duration of storage. The characteristics of Field lifecycle management are:

    • Each field is owned by the message from which it was obtained
    • All fields conceptually go out of scope when their owning message is recycled, after which time any references stored by client code become dangling and any attempt to use them will result in undefined behavior.
    See Also:
    NullField, FieldGroup, NullFieldGroup, Message

      • setMutableCompactDecimal

        Field setMutableCompactDecimal(MutableCompactDecimal value)
        Description copied from interface: FieldValue
        Set the field value as a MutableCompactDecimal.

        Note that, as for other types, this method transfers ownership of the specified value to the Field object. It is more important in this case, however, because of its mutability. That is, if the value is modified after this call then so is the Field object to which ownership was transferred.

        Specified by:
